ref="https://www.nme.com/artists/lionel-richie">Lionel Richie</a> album, but with &#39;(What&#39;s The Story) Morning Glory?&#39; edited in instead. The caption to the post reads, “RIP Matthew Perry”.</p><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="550" data-dnt="true"><p lang="en" dir="ltr"> RIP Matthew Perry. <img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/14.0.0/72x72/1f494.png" alt="💔" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> <a href="https://t.co/lwUyxh7t3h">pic.twitter.com/lwUyxh7t3h</a></p><p> — Anything Oasis Official (@AnythingOasis) <a href="https://twitter.com/AnythingOasis/status/1718712758424731804?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">October 29, 2023</a> </p></blockquote><p><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></p><p> Elsewhere, fans of Perry&#39;s are remembering his various roles across his career, particularly in <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/tv/fans-remembering-matthew-perry-delightful-guest-appearance-the-west-wing-3527858"><em>The West Wing</em></a> , and are continuing to pay tribute to the late actor.</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/tv/oasis-matthew-perry-3528195">Oasis fans are remembering the time Matthew Perry hosted them on &#39;SNL&#39;</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
